{
  "stem": "18581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had all the afternoon and the evening free for studies.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it didn't affect very much.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sometimes, there was some conflict.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it could be resolved with the-- with the professor or with the tutor.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was no-- no big problem.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because I could use-- I could use, there, Lithuanian, Polish that I learned in the meantime, Russian, and Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You must realize that some of the refugees that came from Poland, like [INAUDIBLE] yeshivas, the [?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mir ?] Yeshiva, as an example, and other yeshivas, [NON-ENGLISH] Yeshiva, came-- they run away from Poland to Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had to go through the passport offices.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So sometimes, the yeshiva boys didn't speak even Polish, only spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So at that time, the manager said, Mr.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Trigubovas, he says, this is a client for you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I spoke to them in Yiddish and I found out exactly where they came from.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we used to grant, according to the law and to the situation of every person, each person was to give him either a [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [INAUDIBLE] refugee card-- that's like-- like a [INAUDIBLE] pass-- or a sort of identity card, which did not prove his being a citizen or not.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or a-- a Lithuanian passport.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Besides the yeshiva students that you dealt with from Poland, were there other groups from Poland?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were many Jews.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm sure there were any non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes, of course.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I dealt with many non-Jews that were Poles who ran away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They didn't want to be interned by the Russians or by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Lithuania was a [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] neutral country.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
